<h1 style="text-align:center; color:#000066">
The Holy Spirit<br>
God's Love in Action
</h1>

<p style="text-align:center;">
by <a  href="http://www.christs-light-ministries.org/christine.html">Rev.  Christine Olivares</a><br>
<strong>Evangelist of the Holy Spirit</strong>
</p>

<blockquote>&ldquo;Suddenly a sound like the blowing of a violent wind came from heaven and filled the whole house where they were sitting. They saw what seemed to be tongues of fire that separated and came to rest on each of them. All of them were filled with the Holy Spirit and began to speak in other tongues as the Spirit enabled them.&rdquo; (Acts 2:2-4)</blockquote>

<p>Hello, my name is Christine Olivares, an Evangelist of the Holy Spirit.  This subject has been a passionate one for me, since I have experienced Him in very powerful ways.  I grew up in the Charismatic Movement, and was baptized in the Spirit at age eleven.  The Holy Spirit has done wonders in my life, and my purpose is to bring that same Spirit to you.  I have experienced His gifts and healing power, and want you to experience the same.</p>

<p>My goal is to help you understand the Holy Spirit in different ways and how He can act in your life.  Our goal as Christians is to live the Gospel of Jesus Christ and to bring &ldquo;The Good News.&rdquo; The only way we can do this is through the Holy Spirit.  If He is not in our lives, we cannot move mountains (Matthew 17:20) or be used to perform miracles.  Remember that the Holy Spirit moves the way He wants (John 3:8).  He could manifest in charismatic phenomena, or He could be more subtle in our everyday lives.</p>

<h2>Life in the Spirit</h2>

<p>Today, many hear about the Holy Spirit only in Theological terms.  Some denominations do not understand the Holy Spirit in a profound way.  There is so much discussion of the Holy Spirit, and people wonder whether He is still here today.</p>

<p>We should be living our lives in the Holy Spirit.  If we see people who are sick, we should lay hands on them and pray over them (Matthew 10:8).  Why? This is simple: because we must do what Jesus commissioned us to do.  Jesus did not say we need special gifts of healing to lay hands on the sick.  No, believers are to do this, common people like you and me! We should be casting out demons and healing the sick everywhere we go, not just inside Church walls (Mark 16:17-18).</p>

<p>I believe that Christians are afraid to receive the Holy Spirit because of the powerful ways He transforms.  When the Holy Spirit comes down, there is no turning back.  After we receive the Holy Spirit, we are challenged to walk in the Spirit and live life in the Spirit.  People may also be afraid that they may be listening to themselves rather than the Holy Spirit.  I can say that once the Holy Spirit comes in your life, He will teach you all you need to know.  Mind you, you will make mistakes, but didn't Jesus' disciples make mistakes? Think of Peter who denied Jesus three times (Mark 14:66-72).  Paul and Peter disagreed with each other (Galatians 2:11-21), but they were still strong in the Lord.  Remember that even though you will make mistakes, you will only learn how to overcome them through experience.  Remember that experience is your greatest teacher.</p>

<p>I will teach you how to live the life by walking in the Spirit.  Begin by just being open to the Spirit right now.  As you read this article, ask the Holy Spirit to come into your life and to help you every day.  Be prepared for a life full of miracles and transformation. Nothing is impossible with God (Luke 1:37).</p>

